result.execSummary:
The defendant Jabari D Powell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jabari D Powell is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jabari D Powell was found guilty of Operating A Vehicle Without Owner's Consent (Armed Carjacking) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(1g).
  • Jabari D Powell was found guilty of Possession Of A Dangerous Weapon By Person Under 18, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.60(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Associated with Charge #1/corrected
Case referred back to Court.
Associated with Charge #1

Defendant Jabari D Powell in court with attorney Thomas Holland Reed.  Defendant Jabari D Powell in custody.  John J Rejowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant. Additional statement made by Tammy K.

AS TO COUNT 1: The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 8 YEARS, concurrent to count 3, credit for 140 DAYS time served. The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 3 YEARS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 5 YEARS. Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 4 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 3: Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to count 1, with credit for 140 days served. Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 1 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION/PROBATION:
- Serve 8 MONTHS UPFRONT condition time in the House of Correction (concurrent to both counts).
- Provide a DNA sample. 
- Maintain full-time work or school or combination of both. 
- Not to be present where any guns are present in any vehicle.
- No possession of illegal drugs.
- No contact with victim K.E.K. and co-defendant Tererick Terrell.

- Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA surcharges to be paid during period of probation, if revoked to be paid by defendant's prison funds at a percentage to be determined by the DOC, remainder to be paid during the period of extended supervision; failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

*Court sets restitution at zero.
*Court finds defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program AFTER 18 MONTHS.
*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

- Court orders victim impact sealed and no contact order stating victim's name.
